## Features Verified ✅

### 1. Dragon Alert — Deterioration Detection
At **t=945 min** (past the sepsis ramp at t=700), the system correctly detected deterioration:
- Risk gauge jumped to **62% (HIGH RISK)**
- 🐉 **DRAGON ALERT** banner fired with pulsing fiery border
- Vitals showed: HR 100 bpm (+24.5), SpO₂ 91.1% (-5.9), RR 28 (+12.4), Temp 38.3°C (+1.51)

![Dragon Alert at t=945 with 62% risk, showing deteriorated vitals and fiery alert banner](C:/Users/eshav/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6b34ef5e-e4fa-4b43-90e4-46061df6bbcb/dragon_alert.png)

### 2. What-If Intervention Simulator
With Fluid Bolus set to **400-500ml**, the green "tamed" trajectory appeared on the risk plot, showing a **10% risk reduction**. The What-If result card updates in real time.

![What-If with 400ml fluid bolus applied, showing intervention effect](C:/Users/eshav/.gemini/antigravity/brain/6b34ef5e-e4fa-4b43-90e4-46061df6bbcb/bottom_panel.png)

### 3. SHAP Explainability
**SpO₂** identified as the **top risk contributor at 26%** using SHAP KernelExplainer — clinically correct since SpO₂ drops are the hallmark of sepsis deterioration.

### 4. All Dashboard Components Working
- ✅ 5 vital sign metrics with colored deltas
- ✅ Plotly vitals chart with LSTM forecast (dashed lines)
- ✅ Risk trajectory with red (no intervention) vs green (with intervention) overlay
- ✅ Risk gauge (color-coded: green → yellow → orange → red)
- ✅ Adaptive thresholds table with breach status
- ✅ False alarm reduction counter
- ✅ Projected clinical impact bar chart (25% mortality reduction, 58% alarm reduction)
- ✅ Override / Escalate / Audit Log buttons
- ✅ Business model card
- ✅ Ethics footer (ICMR compliant, decision-support only)

### 5. Full Browser Recording

